The crystal structure of pentasodium hydrogen dicitrate, $\mathrm{Na}{ }_{5} \mathrm{H}\left(\mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}\right)_{2}$, has been solved and refined using synchrotron X-ray powder diffraction data, and optimized using density functional techniques. Each of the two independent citrate anions is joined into a dimer by very strong centrosymmetric $\mathrm{O}-\mathrm{H} \cdots \mathrm{O}$ hydrogen bonds, with O $\cdots$ O distances of $2.419$ and $2.409 \AA$. Four octahedrally coordinated $\mathrm{Na}^{+}$ions share edges to form open layers parallel to the $a b$ plane. A fifth $\mathrm{Na}^{+}$ion in trigonal-bipyramidal coordination shares faces with $\mathrm{NaO}_{6}$ octahedra on both sides of these layers.

\section{Chemical context}
In the course of a systematic study of the crystal structures of Group 1 (alkali metal) citrate salts to understand the anion's conformational flexibility, ionization, coordination tendencies, and hydrogen bonding, we have determined several new crystal structures. Most of the new structures were solved using X-ray powder diffraction data (laboratory and/or synchrotron), but single crystals were used where available. The general trends and conclusions about the sixteen new compounds and twelve previously characterized structures are being reported separately (Rammohan \& Kaduk, 2017a). Nine of the new structures - $\mathrm{NaKHC}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}, \mathrm{NaK}_{2} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}$, $\mathrm{Na}_{3} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}, \quad \mathrm{NaH}_{2} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}, \quad \mathrm{Na}_{2} \mathrm{HC}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}, \quad \mathrm{~K}_{3} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}$, $\mathrm{Rb}_{2} \mathrm{HC}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}, \mathrm{Rb}_{3} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}\left(\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}\right)$, and $\mathrm{Rb}_{3} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}-$ have been published recently (Rammohan \& Kaduk, 2016a,b,c,d,e, $2017 b, c, d$; Rammohan et al., 2016), and two additional structures $-\mathrm{KH}_{2} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}$ and $\mathrm{KH}_{2} \mathrm{C}_{6} \mathrm{H}_{5} \mathrm{O}_{7}\left(\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}\right)_{2}$ - have been communicated to the CSD (Kaduk \& Stern, 2016a,b).

